        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer586777764" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12098395265205694291">It&apos;s hard to appreciate essays about books which one has yet to read; thus, I enjoyed the pieces about literature and writing as a whole more than I did the selections about specific titles. But all of it was interesting. Calvino is my favorite author and his insights into literature are as wide-ranging and devoted as his fiction. Plus, I came across a number of words I&apos;d never heard: mastodonic, gnosiology, and eudaemonism.</span>
